  "market_context": "After a prior long position was active, price formed another bullish break of structure with inefficiency, breaking through supply zones. A demand zone was identified near 1.05560, with a dynamic trend line and liquidity pool above it.",
  "key_observation": "Price created a bullish break of structure with inefficiency, confirming continuation; a demand zone at ~1.05560 aligned with an order block, and a bullish dynamic trend line above created a liquidity pool to be swept.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified a new bullish break of structure accompanied by inefficiency, indicating strong continuation potential.",
    "Step 2: Located the demand zone associated with the recent bullish wave, centered around 1.05560 on the 1-minute chart.",
    "Step 3: Noted a bullish dynamic trend line just above the demand zone, forming a liquidity pool (SSL/BSL context) that would likely be swept before upward continuation.",
    "Step 4: Placed a buy limit order at the highest point of the order block within the demand zone, targeting the swing high at 1.05690 as take profit.",
    "Step 5: Applied position sizing rule: second order size reduced to half of the first position, respecting the max three concurrent trades rule."
  ],
  "outcome": "Buy order activated; price moved upward as anticipated and hit the target (TP at 1.05690).",
  "lessons": "Continuation trades after a valid BOS with inefficiency can be reliably taken in the same direction as the trend, especially when a demand zone aligns with an order block and liquidity above is present for a sweep.",
